message.content:
cs.NI, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the introduction of SDN in core networks and presents an FPGA-based switch that is compliant with OpenFlow, a protocol for SDN.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on the design and implementation of an FPGA-based switch architecture.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the need for scalability and flexibility in modern networking infrastructure, which can be seen as a control problem.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as SDN is often used in data center networks to improve network management and resource allocation.
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is also a possible category as the FPGA-based switch architecture can be seen as an embedded system.
